cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a method for text-to-image synthesis using generative adversarial networks (GANs) and focuses on object-centered synthesis for complex scenes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision) which deals with image processing and analysis. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for text description, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of GANs for image synthesis indicates it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.GR (Graphics).
